{
  "rules": [
    {
      "description": "Enforce project coding standards and structure",
      "technology_stack": ["Next.js", "Python", "FastAPI"],
      "rules": [
        "Use functional components and hooks in React.",
        "Prefer const over let where variables are immutable.",
        "Follow Airbnb's JavaScript/TypeScript style guide.",
        "Use camelCase for variables and PascalCase for components."
      ]
    },
    {
      "description": "Frontend development conventions",
      "technology_stack": ["Next.js", "React", "Styled-components"],
      "rules": [
        "Use Next.js for routing and page creation.",
        "Use Redux for state management.",
        "Write CSS using Styled-components.",
        "Dynamic import for lazy-loading components."
      ]
    },
    {
      "description": "Backend development with Python and FastAPI",
      "technology_stack": ["Python", "FastAPI"],
      "rules": [
        "Implement RESTful services using FastAPI.",
        "Use Pydantic for data validation and type annotation.",
        "Handle asynchronous operations with async/await.",
        "Organize code into routers and models."
      ]
    },
    {
      "description": "Testing practices",
      "technology_stack": ["Jest", "React Testing Library"],
      "rules": [
        "Target at least 80% test coverage.",
        "Write unit and snapshot tests for components.",
        "Mock API calls in tests."
      ]
    },
    {
      "description": "Performance optimization",
      "technology_stack": ["Next.js", "React"],
      "rules": [
        "Use React.memo for memoization.",
        "Optimize useEffect hooks and limit re-renders.",
        "Implement code splitting via dynamic imports."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
Here is a list of updated documentation for the chosen technologies:

Next.js: https://nextjs.org/docs
React: https://react.dev/
TypeScript: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/
Redux: https://redux.js.org/
Styled-components: https://styled-components.com/docs
Jest: https://jestjs.io/docs/getting-started
React Testing Library: https://testing-library.com/docs/react-testing-library/intro/
FastAPI: https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/
Python: https://docs.python.org/3/

Always lookup the documentation of the technologies used in the project, to find the best practices and right versions to use.
In the document @Prosjekt.txt in the root catalog, you will find the project description and other relevant information on how to build the project.
